  "prompt": "What should my board exam percentage be to get admission to St. Xaviers in Kolkata for a BSC in mathematics? Does St. Xaviers consider only mathematics marks as criteria for admission?",
  "response": "Getting into St. Xavier's Kolkata for a BSc in Mathematics is competitive. Here's a breakdown of what you should aim for in terms of board exam percentage and other admission factors:\n\n**1. Target Board Exam Percentage:**\n\n*   **General Category:** Aim for **95% or above overall** in your best four subjects (including Mathematics and English). The higher, the better.\n*   **Reserved Categories (SC/ST/OBC-A/OBC-B):** The cutoffs are generally lower for reserved categories. However, aim for at least **90% or above** to have a strong chance. Refer to the college website for category-specific criteria.\n*   **Important Consideration:** Cutoffs fluctuate each year based on the performance of applicants. So, these percentages are indicative, not definitive.\n\n**2. Does St. Xavier's consider only Mathematics marks?**\n\n*   **No, St. Xavier's considers an aggregate of your \"Best Four\" subjects.** This usually includes:\n    *   English\n    *   Mathematics\n    *   And the best two other subjects from your board exams.\n\n*   **However, Mathematics is a mandatory subject** for BSc Mathematics. Failing to have Mathematics as a subject in your 10+2 will make you ineligible for the course.\n\n*   **A good score in Mathematics is extremely important.** While they calculate an aggregate, strong performance in Mathematics will significantly boost your chances.\n\n**3. Other Factors to Keep in Mind:**\n\n*   **Online Application Form:** Fill out the online application form on the St. Xavier's College, Kolkata website accurately and within the stipulated deadline.\n*   **Entrance Exam (If Applicable):** While they primarily rely on board exam scores, St. Xavier's *sometimes* conducts entrance exams or interviews (especially if there is a tie between candidates with the same aggregate). Check the admission notification for the current year to confirm if an entrance exam will be conducted.\n*   **Interview (If Applicable):** If shortlisted, you might be called for an interview. Be prepared to discuss your interest in mathematics, your academic background, and your future goals. Be confident and articulate your thoughts clearly.\n*   **Extracurricular Activities (Limited Weightage):** St. Xavier's is known for its holistic approach, but for BSc Mathematics, academic performance carries the most weight. Extracurricular activities and achievements might give you a marginal advantage, especially if there's a tie, but they won't compensate for significantly lower board exam scores.\n*   **Christian Minority Quota:** If you belong to the Christian community, you may have an advantage under the Christian Minority Quota, but you will need to provide the necessary documents and certificates.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\n*   Your board exam percentage is the most crucial factor.\n*   Aim for the highest possible score, especially in Mathematics and English.\n*   Stay updated with the official St. Xavier's College, Kolkata website for the latest admission notifications, cutoff marks, and admission procedures.\n*   Prepare for a potential interview by brushing up on your mathematical concepts and thinking about why you want to study mathematics at St. Xavier's.\n\nGood luck with your applications!\n",
